## Test it

```bash
# find a real image tag
aws ecr list-images --repository-name mini-deploy-platform-app --profile limonlab

# send a deploy request
aws sqs send-message \
  --queue-url $(aws sqs get-queue-url --queue-name mini-deploy-platform-deploy-queue --query QueueUrl --output text --profile limonlab) \
  --message-body '{"image_tag": "<REAL_SHA>", "requested_by": "me"}' \
  --profile limonlab

# watch it work
aws logs tail /aws/lambda/mini-deploy-platform-deploy-worker --follow --profile limonlab
```

A **bad** tag should fail at the Lambda and land in the DLQ (not deploy). A **real** tag
should register a new revision and roll it out.

